                "imgDesc": "<p>Energy blocks can be naturally occurring or artificially created, and are separated into Pneuma Blocks and Ousia Blocks. After collecting an energy block, your next <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">Normal, Charged, or Plunging Attack</span> will, upon hit, release the energy stored within them. This will come in handy when adventuring in a place like Fontaine.</p>",
                "key": "Page 1/2"
              },
              {
                "img": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/09/17/94376896/50a9265d930b9237ad84b687f08e22ab_3283540192582944474.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>With the aid of these energy blocks, characters can unleash Pneuma or Ousia energies even while <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">underwater</span>.</p><p>Most characters from Fontaine have an Arkhe, and thus can use their attacks to trigger energies <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">corresponding to their Arkhe attribute</span> underwater without the use of Pneumousia Blocks.</p>",
                "key": "Page 2/2"
              }
            ],
